The paper addresses the problem of securing networked cyber-physical systems against attacks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also deals with the control of physical plants using multiple sensors and actuators communicating over a network, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of watermarking as a technique to secure the system, which is a topic that falls under the categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and software engineering (cs.SE).
